.TH init 1  "init " 
.SH NAME
init \- Scaffold a `.wafrift.toml` config in the current directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBinit\fR [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scaffold a `.wafrift.toml` config in the current directory
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output path for the scaffold. Defaults to `./.wafrift.toml`
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Overwrite the file if it already exists. Without this flag, init refuses to clobber an existing config — operators have no expectation that `wafrift init` would destroy in\-flight tuning
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
